<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="107" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,1598,2093]" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">
Plants cespitose. Culms homomorphic, erect below, arching and clambering above, often supported by trees, 
<quantity box="[136,244,1670,1697]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.125" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.25" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" unit="m" value="11.25" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="2.5">2.5–20 m</quantity>
tall, infra- and supranodal bands of trichomes usually absent [present in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Trinius 1835: 626) Londono" authorityName="Londono" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Trinius" baseAuthorityPageNumber="626" baseAuthorityYear="1835" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eremocaulon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitatum">
<emphasis box="[1077,1222,1671,1696]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">E. capitatum</emphasis>
(Trinius 1835: 626) Londoño
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G." box="[273,618,1706,1733]" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" pagination="703 - 721" refId="ref25388" refString="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G. (2002) A revision of the brazilian bamboo genus Eremocaulon (Poaceae: Bambuseae: Guaduinae). Systematic Botany 27 (4): 703 - 721. https: // dx. doi. org / 10.1043 / 0363 - 6445 - 27.4.703" type="journal article" year="2002">Londoño &amp; Clark (2002: 714)</bibRefCitation>
]. Branch complement with one dominant and smaller secondary branches, without thorns. Culm leaves and foliage leaves clearly distinct. Culm leaves not clearly differentiated along the culm, with reflexed blades, narrower than the sheath summit, sheath fimbriae present. Foliage leaf sheaths with fimbriae at the apex or not, translucent swelling absent, outer ligule present, blades narrowly triangular, ovate-lanceolate or linear-lanceolate, midnerve prominent. Synflorescences terminal to leafy, indeterminate, 1–15 pseudospikelets per coflorescence, coflorescences either with one to few pseudospikelets and open or with several to many pseudospikelets and congested to capitate, each coflorescence and paraclade or pseudospikelet with one subtending bract; pseudospikelets sessile, bisexual, glumes absent, comprising 1 prophyll, 0–4 gemmiparous bracts, with 1–17 fertile anthecium, smooth, and with 1–4 terminal rudimentary anthecium. Fruit a basic caryopsis, hilum linear, as long as the caryopsis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,1598,2093]" lastBlockId="9.[136,1451,158,293]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="108" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Soderstrom &amp; Londono" authorityYear="1987" box="[189,339,2030,2056]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eremocaulon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,339,2030,2056]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Eremocaulon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a woody bamboo genus endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[783,851,2030,2056]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G." box="[867,1138,2030,2056]" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" pagination="703 - 721" refId="ref25388" refString="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G. (2002) A revision of the brazilian bamboo genus Eremocaulon (Poaceae: Bambuseae: Guaduinae). Systematic Botany 27 (4): 703 - 721. https: // dx. doi. org / 10.1043 / 0363 - 6445 - 27.4.703" type="journal article" year="2002">Londoño &amp; Clark 2002</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kellogg, E. A." box="[1150,1307,2030,2057]" pageId="8" pageNumber="107" refId="ref25159" refString="Kellogg, E. A. (2015) The Families and Genera of Vascular Plants Volume XIII. Flowering Plants Monocots: Poaceae. Springer International Publishing, Switzerland, 413 pp." type="book" year="2015">Kellogg 2015</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Jesus-Costa, C. &amp; Clark, L. G. &amp; Santos-Goncalves, A. P. &amp; Londono, X." pageId="8" pageNumber="107" pagination="104 - 112" refId="ref24778" refString="Jesus-Costa, C., Clark, L. G., Santos-Goncalves, A. P. &amp; Londono, X. (2018) Eremocaulon triramis (Poaceae: Bambusoideae: Bambuseae: Guaduinae): a new species from the Atlantic rainforest of the State of Espirito Santo, Brazil. Phytotaxa 375 (1): 104 - 112. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 375.1.7" type="journal article" year="2018">
Jesus-Costa 
<emphasis box="[136,192,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="107">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). It is characterized by its branch complement with one dominant and smaller secondary branches, without thorns, infra- and supranodal bands of trichomes absent (present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Londono" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Trinius" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[904,1048,159,184]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Eremocaulon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="9" pageNumber="108" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="capitatum">
<emphasis box="[904,1048,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="108">E. capitatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), culm leaves with reflexed blades, narrower than the sheath, foliage leaves with midnerve prominent and synflorescences composed of pseudospikelets (
<bibRefCitation author="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G." box="[144,409,230,256]" pageId="9" pageNumber="108" pagination="703 - 721" refId="ref25388" refString="Londono, X. &amp; Clark, L. G. (2002) A revision of the brazilian bamboo genus Eremocaulon (Poaceae: Bambuseae: Guaduinae). Systematic Botany 27 (4): 703 - 721. https: // dx. doi. org / 10.1043 / 0363 - 6445 - 27.4.703" type="journal article" year="2002">Londoño &amp; Clark 2002</bibRefCitation>
). The genus has five species in the Amazon, Cerrado and Mata Atlântica domains (
<bibRefCitation author="Lopes-Neto, R. B. &amp; Viana, P. L. &amp; Shirasuna, R. T." pageId="9" pageNumber="108" refId="ref25504" refString="Lopes-Neto, R. B., Viana, P. L. &amp; Shirasuna, R. T. (2020) Eremocaulon in Flora do Brasil 2020, Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro state, Brazil. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 13226 (accessed 9 October 2021)." type="url" year="2020">
Lopes-Neto 
<emphasis box="[136,192,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="108">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). In the Serra do Cachimbo, the genus is represented by one species.
</paragraph>
